WEBVTT

1
00:00:58.208 --> 00:01:00.333
You're working for SherKhan?

2
00:01:02.750 --> 00:01:04.916
SherKhan is working for him.
don't you get it?

3
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:07.583
I don't work for nobody. I work for us.

4
00:01:07.666 --> 00:01:09.000
Fuck that!

5
00:01:09.083 --> 00:01:13.125
So having me beaten up was
all for us too? Why do you keep lying?

6
00:01:15.291 --> 00:01:18.333
Look at this bullshit!
When are you gonna cut the crap. huh?

7
00:01:18.416 --> 00:01:20.291
Who's Milord? I don't get it.

8
00:01:20.375 --> 00:01:21.541
He's the boss.

9
00:01:22.041 --> 00:01:25.791
He's Fatso's boss.
He had me beaten up. that's who he is.

10
00:01:26.458 --> 00:01:28.208
The biggest dealer in Fort-de-France.

11
00:01:29.166 --> 00:01:31.875
You dealing crack. Kylian?
What are you dealing?

12
00:01:31.958 --> 00:01:33.416
Never crack.

13
00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:35.666
I promise I'd never touch that shit.

14
00:01:38.791 --> 00:01:39.916
Okay.

15
00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:45.666
I know this might be tough to understand.
but it's for our own wellbeing.

16
00:01:45.750 --> 00:01:46.750
All of us.

17
00:01:46.833 --> 00:01:49.750
Crack isn't gonna
keep a roof over our heads.

18
00:01:51.833 --> 00:01:53.875
You dealing? What. weed?

19
00:01:54.791 --> 00:01:57.250
Which block? Fuck's sake. Kylian. explain!

20
00:01:57.333 --> 00:01:59.291
I'm not on the streets.

21
00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:02.583
I dealt a bit of pot
to get enough cash to buy coke.

22
00:02:05.291 --> 00:02:06.666
No one knows who I am.

23
00:02:06.750 --> 00:02:08.500
Trust me. it's safer that way.

24
00:02:08.583 --> 00:02:12.000
I sell the coke where
it earns me the most. in France.

25
00:02:12.916 --> 00:02:15.125
I mean. I will be soon.

26
00:02:15.208 --> 00:02:16.541
I just closed a huge deal.

27
00:02:16.625 --> 00:02:18.833
I got merchandise coming in overseas.

28
00:02:18.916 --> 00:02:20.083
We're talking millions.

29
00:02:21.958 --> 00:02:23.500
Completely insane. this guy.

30
00:02:25.166 --> 00:02:27.916
- We gotta do something.
- See a therapist?

31
00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:30.125
FATSO - Everything was stolen.
there's nothing left.

32
00:02:30.208 --> 00:02:32.458
I guess it's to be expected
with Mama's death.

33
00:02:32.541 --> 00:02:33.958
He's not coping. We didn't see it.

34
00:02:34.041 --> 00:02:35.958
WE'RE CHANGING HIDEOUTS.
I'LL CALL YOU AFTER.

35
00:02:36.041 --> 00:02:37.041
He's losing it.

36
00:02:41.458 --> 00:02:43.166
It's true. he's Milord.

37
00:02:45.125 --> 00:02:47.125
Milord was Dylan. It connects.

38
00:02:48.541 --> 00:02:53.333
So this son of a bitch swiped
Dylan's username to sell goddamn poison?

39
00:02:54.291 --> 00:02:55.791
That is disgusting.

40
00:02:58.041 --> 00:02:59.541
How long have you been doing this?

41
00:03:02.833 --> 00:03:05.041
Answer her. Milord. or whatever!

42
00:03:06.583 --> 00:03:07.833
Two years. maybe.

43
00:03:09.291 --> 00:03:11.208
Nah. he's being played for sure.

44
00:03:11.291 --> 00:03:14.625
Marv. there's an apartment
full of their shit. It's a huge operation.

45
00:03:15.375 --> 00:03:16.833
Two years.

46
00:03:17.750 --> 00:03:19.166
We were always together in school.

47
00:03:19.958 --> 00:03:21.916
- Had to keep it a secret.
- Stop talking!

48
00:03:30.166 --> 00:03:34.041
Aren't you all fed up. though?
Living in this shack. counting pennies?

49
00:03:34.708 --> 00:03:37.166
Not being able to afford a damn gas stove?

50
00:03:37.750 --> 00:03:40.875
Having to hide the babies
'cause we're too poor for custody?

51
00:03:40.958 --> 00:03:42.583
Who do you think got the damn stove?

52
00:03:43.333 --> 00:03:45.458
How do you think we got the stand back?

53
00:03:45.541 --> 00:03:49.875
It's the best solution to use Milord.
Yeah. it might be hard. but that's life.

54
00:03:52.458 --> 00:03:53.833
You say a shack?

55
00:03:55.500 --> 00:03:57.791
You wouldn't have dared
talk like that in front of Mama.

56
00:04:01.666 --> 00:04:04.625
- Take your things. get out of here.
- Marv--

57
00:04:04.708 --> 00:04:06.333
I said take your shit

58
00:04:06.416 --> 00:04:09.333
and find somewhere else to stay.
'cause you can't stay here.

59
00:04:09.416 --> 00:04:12.583
Better to keep it secret.
It was to keep you out of the mix.

60
00:04:12.666 --> 00:04:16.666
Don't give me that bull like
you're a gangster! Life isn't a movie!

61
00:04:17.583 --> 00:04:20.583
You had better knock this shit off.
I mean it. It's pathetic.

62
00:04:23.791 --> 00:04:24.875
Get out.

63
00:04:35.458 --> 00:04:37.791
Hey! Give me that ring!

64
00:04:37.875 --> 00:04:40.166
Mama thought you were pure. you bastard.

65
00:04:40.250 --> 00:04:41.250
You realize that?

66
00:04:41.333 --> 00:04:43.000
Give it back. now.

67
00:04:46.125 --> 00:04:47.208
No.

68
00:05:30.458 --> 00:05:33.541
KIKI
I'm sorry

69
00:06:55.166 --> 00:06:56.791
I DON'T HAVE
THE STRENGTH ANYMORE

70
00:07:16.791 --> 00:07:18.250
Hard to believe. huh?

71
00:07:29.166 --> 00:07:30.250
XHESUS
I miss you already

72
00:07:30.333 --> 00:07:32.791
The weather's nice. I'm thinking of you…
What are you doing?

73
00:07:32.875 --> 00:07:34.708
Why aren't you answering?
Is there a problem?

74
00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:36.916
Why's this guy being a dick?

75
00:08:05.625 --> 00:08:07.583
Fuck this. Shit.

76
00:08:25.750 --> 00:08:27.958
I appreciate it.
It will just be for tonight.

77
00:08:28.041 --> 00:08:29.833
Don't worry. my mom knows.

78
00:08:36.666 --> 00:08:38.625
You get in a fight with your brothers?

79
00:08:40.083 --> 00:08:41.875
It'll blow over. I'm sure it will.

80
00:08:48.041 --> 00:08:49.416
Won't be that simple. I'm afraid.

81
00:08:50.833 --> 00:08:52.750
It will! That's family.

82
00:08:55.125 --> 00:08:56.583
You don't know my family.

83
00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:05.000
Want to drink something?

84
00:09:06.083 --> 00:09:07.208
If you are.

85
00:09:30.750 --> 00:09:33.416
FATSO
Where have you moved to?

86
00:09:43.166 --> 00:09:44.166
Enter.

87
00:10:01.125 --> 00:10:03.833
I just want to talk with you.

88
00:10:13.750 --> 00:10:15.916
We've just lost our mother.
You know that. I imagine.

89
00:10:22.333 --> 00:10:25.250
I'm worried about Kylian.
He's my responsibility.

90
00:10:26.625 --> 00:10:28.250
He's grieving. He needs structure.

91
00:10:29.541 --> 00:10:31.041
And what he's doing with you here…

92
00:10:31.916 --> 00:10:34.750
this shit is the exact opposite
of what he actually needs right now.

93
00:10:35.500 --> 00:10:39.125
Anyway. all this to say.
you're gonna have to do this without him.

94
00:10:39.208 --> 00:10:40.625
I'm serious. he's done.

95
00:10:42.458 --> 00:10:45.125
- Look. I'm not sure exactly what he said--
- That's not the issue!

96
00:10:45.208 --> 00:10:47.250
I know all about your thing.

97
00:10:47.333 --> 00:10:49.833
And I will not let him
be involved any longer.

98
00:10:50.333 --> 00:10:52.833
All I'm asking is let him be.

99
00:10:54.125 --> 00:10:56.541
Marvin… our business don't work like that.

100
00:10:56.625 --> 00:10:58.041
- Mmm.
- Alexy?

101
00:10:58.791 --> 00:11:01.041
This is happening. you guys hear me?

102
00:11:02.250 --> 00:11:05.916
Look. you're all adults. You know
you can work with anybody you want.

103
00:11:07.791 --> 00:11:10.708
And. anyway. I'm gonna
be on that kid like white on rice.

104
00:11:11.291 --> 00:11:12.875
So there's nothing you can do.

105
00:11:13.375 --> 00:11:15.125
You might want to be careful.

106
00:11:15.208 --> 00:11:16.916
Kylian is 16!

107
00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:20.708
He thinks he's some kinda boss.
He's gonna fall flat on his ass.

108
00:11:21.541 --> 00:11:23.333
He won't go to prison.

109
00:11:23.416 --> 00:11:24.833
But you?

110
00:11:24.916 --> 00:11:26.875
You're all over 18.

111
00:11:28.041 --> 00:11:29.166
You realize that?

112
00:11:29.250 --> 00:11:31.750
Do your business without Kylian.

113
00:11:33.750 --> 00:11:36.083
You just gonna let him go like that?

114
00:11:36.166 --> 00:11:38.458
It's disrespectful. man.

115
00:11:38.541 --> 00:11:39.791
Crazy.

116
00:11:41.333 --> 00:11:42.750
We'll handle it.

117
00:12:17.666 --> 00:12:19.000
My uncle's here.

118
00:12:19.583 --> 00:12:20.583
And?

119
00:12:21.291 --> 00:12:24.333
Why does he have to show up at 7:00 a.m.?

120
00:12:24.416 --> 00:12:26.250
He always come this early?

121
00:12:26.333 --> 00:12:27.333
Yeah.

122
00:12:27.916 --> 00:12:31.166
My mother works with him…
for him at city hall.

123
00:12:32.041 --> 00:12:33.041
It's fine.

124
00:12:33.125 --> 00:12:34.125
'Kay.

125
00:12:38.875 --> 00:12:40.583
Are you coming with me to Claire's party?

126
00:12:42.083 --> 00:12:43.166
It's a costume party.

127
00:12:43.250 --> 00:12:45.416
- Got anything white?
- No.

128
00:12:45.500 --> 00:12:46.666
Okay.

129
00:12:46.750 --> 00:12:48.208
I'll just bring you one.

130
00:12:48.291 --> 00:12:50.208
Can dress up as Tony Montana.

131
00:12:50.291 --> 00:12:51.750
I'll be Michelle Pfeiffer.

132
00:12:56.916 --> 00:12:59.041
Seriously? You were here yesterday.

133
00:12:59.125 --> 00:13:01.875
Sorry. Yes. but the contractor's
being a pain in the ass.

134
00:13:01.958 --> 00:13:02.958
Really.

135
00:13:03.583 --> 00:13:04.583
Hi.

136
00:13:06.541 --> 00:13:08.625
- Morning.
- You sleep okay?

137
00:13:08.708 --> 00:13:09.708
Yeah. fine.

138
00:13:10.208 --> 00:13:11.416
Same. thanks.

139
00:13:17.333 --> 00:13:20.291
If you can be ready in ten minutes.
I'll drop you off.

140
00:13:20.375 --> 00:13:21.375
Okay.

141
00:13:41.791 --> 00:13:43.000
Alex Croquet.

142
00:13:44.500 --> 00:13:46.250
I know. Kylian Lafleur.

143
00:13:47.416 --> 00:13:48.833
I know you too.

144
00:13:50.208 --> 00:13:52.083
Lily has spoken of you.

145
00:13:54.208 --> 00:13:55.666
Your mother just passed.

146
00:13:56.250 --> 00:13:57.500
Tough life.

147
00:14:01.416 --> 00:14:03.416
Go tell your mother I'm heading out.

148
00:14:17.375 --> 00:14:18.541
Lafleur.

149
00:14:21.291 --> 00:14:23.250
Can't say Lily hit the jackpot. huh?

150
00:14:30.500 --> 00:14:31.916
Just how many are in your family?

151
00:14:33.958 --> 00:14:34.791
A lot.

152
00:14:38.666 --> 00:14:39.916
So you've lost count too.

153
00:14:44.375 --> 00:14:47.000
So. to summarize.

154
00:14:48.458 --> 00:14:51.166
you're kicked out
and you're mooching off the Juliards.

155
00:14:51.791 --> 00:14:53.166
What's your plan?

156
00:14:54.958 --> 00:14:57.958
Don't tell me the others
will be showing up here as well.

157
00:15:06.208 --> 00:15:07.708
It's not sustainable.

158
00:15:09.250 --> 00:15:10.250
What?

159
00:15:11.083 --> 00:15:12.583
Your plan.

160
00:15:15.250 --> 00:15:18.125
Your kind's all bloodsuckers.
I see 'em every day.

161
00:15:20.541 --> 00:15:22.583
Not your fault.
you were just brought up that way.

162
00:15:26.041 --> 00:15:27.666
It won't be here. Kylian.

163
00:15:29.541 --> 00:15:30.541
Not my family.

164
00:15:31.625 --> 00:15:33.416
Find yourself another Lily. champ.

165
00:15:37.041 --> 00:15:38.458
Get out of here.

166
00:15:39.291 --> 00:15:40.791
Go steal yourself a bike.

167
00:15:47.375 --> 00:15:48.958
Get your ass out.

168
00:17:05.083 --> 00:17:06.875
Oh. hello. Kylian.

169
00:17:06.958 --> 00:17:08.958
- Doing well. Mrs. Torville?
- Oh. yes.

170
00:17:09.041 --> 00:17:10.041
Doing well.

171
00:17:10.666 --> 00:17:12.041
Uh. where's Alexy?

172
00:17:12.125 --> 00:17:13.500
He didn't tell me anything.

173
00:17:13.583 --> 00:17:16.583
Just asked me to come by
to clean the place up a little.

174
00:17:17.125 --> 00:17:18.750
He leave any message for me?

175
00:17:18.833 --> 00:17:20.375
No. I'm afraid not.

176
00:17:21.125 --> 00:17:21.958
Thanks.

177
00:18:17.041 --> 00:18:19.166
Mrs. Torville.
may I please borrow your phone?

178
00:18:19.250 --> 00:18:21.166
- Mine is out of battery.
- Here.

179
00:18:23.166 --> 00:18:24.250
Thank you.

180
00:18:37.166 --> 00:18:39.583
- <i>Yes. Grandma?</i>
- Where are you?

181
00:18:41.250 --> 00:18:43.458
<i>- Forget it.</i>
- You for real?

182
00:18:43.541 --> 00:18:44.541
<i>Very.</i>

183
00:18:45.291 --> 00:18:48.916
Listen up. meet me on the field tomorrow.
You better be there.

184
00:19:08.833 --> 00:19:10.041
You alone?

185
00:19:13.625 --> 00:19:14.625
So what now?

186
00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:18.541
- Where's that tool you borrowed?
- Yo. I promise I don't have it.

187
00:19:19.041 --> 00:19:20.875
- I need it.
- What for?

188
00:19:22.250 --> 00:19:24.000
- You don't have it?
- No.

189
00:19:24.083 --> 00:19:25.208
King threw it away.

190
00:19:26.333 --> 00:19:27.500
Hang on.

191
00:19:35.250 --> 00:19:36.541
What are you doing?

192
00:19:39.541 --> 00:19:41.791
What do you want me to do with that?

193
00:19:41.875 --> 00:19:44.583
Man. I got you! It's real!

194
00:19:54.875 --> 00:19:57.500
That way. I can have it on me
without anyone knowing.

195
00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:03.250
Thanks. my man.

196
00:20:03.333 --> 00:20:05.125
Go pay respects to Mama's grave.

197
00:20:05.708 --> 00:20:06.625
Do I have to?

198
00:20:08.166 --> 00:20:09.041
Yes.

199
00:20:16.750 --> 00:20:17.916
Will you tell Milord?

200
00:20:21.708 --> 00:20:24.958
- What?
- Will you tell Milord I helped out?

201
00:20:29.416 --> 00:20:30.500
Yeah. I'll tell him.

202
00:20:35.041 --> 00:20:38.500
- Yo. pour me another shot.
- You're gonna drain the bottle.

203
00:20:43.208 --> 00:20:44.958
Thought I asked you to watch the bar.

204
00:20:45.041 --> 00:20:47.500
Well. I'm watching someone else
while you're here.

205
00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:51.375
- You in love or what?
- I'm pissed off at this man.

206
00:20:52.166 --> 00:20:54.166
He better be ready if I see him.

207
00:20:54.708 --> 00:20:58.083
And you in love with SherKhan or what?
Why are you eyeballing him?

208
00:20:59.375 --> 00:21:02.166
Remember that bastard
returned our cash to SherKhan?

209
00:21:03.250 --> 00:21:05.791
You forget all the risks
you took for that money?

210
00:21:07.166 --> 00:21:08.958
Of course I haven't forgotten.

211
00:21:09.666 --> 00:21:11.458
Well. we're getting it back.

212
00:21:11.958 --> 00:21:15.250
It's ours.
Just gotta find out where it's hidden.

213
00:21:21.833 --> 00:21:22.958
Follow the next guy.

214
00:21:23.041 --> 00:21:25.875
Yeah. okay.

215
00:22:27.750 --> 00:22:28.625
Hello.

216
00:22:28.708 --> 00:22:29.958
Hello.

217
00:22:42.916 --> 00:22:44.750
I thought I saw
your ugly-ass face. Lafleur.

218
00:22:44.833 --> 00:22:46.625
- What you want?
- The fuck you care?

219
00:22:46.708 --> 00:22:49.833
- You following me?
- You think you're a star. is that it?

220
00:22:49.916 --> 00:22:50.916
Doing my nails.

221
00:22:55.791 --> 00:22:56.791
I'll wait outside.

222
00:22:56.875 --> 00:22:58.166
If you want.

223
00:23:00.791 --> 00:23:02.250
Okay. what do you want?

224
00:23:03.541 --> 00:23:04.625
Cheapest.

225
00:23:04.708 --> 00:23:07.333
Basic manicure. five euros.

226
00:23:07.416 --> 00:23:08.416
Perfect!

227
00:23:21.541 --> 00:23:24.458
Your little buddies'll love this.
See ya. homo.

228
00:23:28.125 --> 00:23:29.708
I don't care. Go on.

229
00:23:35.833 --> 00:23:37.083
That's not bad.

230
00:23:38.250 --> 00:23:40.708
I like guys
who take pride in their appearance.

231
00:23:42.916 --> 00:23:45.791
Well. what do you want from me now?

232
00:23:46.666 --> 00:23:50.791
It's a shame what happened the other day.
Didn't get to know each other.

233
00:23:52.041 --> 00:23:53.500
Nicely put.

234
00:23:54.666 --> 00:23:56.083
What do you want?

235
00:23:56.166 --> 00:23:57.750
Just a little spying.

236
00:23:58.541 --> 00:23:59.625
On who?

237
00:24:00.125 --> 00:24:02.916
SherKhan's crew. They know me.

238
00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:04.041
SherKhan again?

239
00:24:04.750 --> 00:24:07.291
- You're obsessed!
- I'll give you five grand.

240
00:24:11.375 --> 00:24:13.083
Plus 50% of what you make.

241
00:24:13.166 --> 00:24:15.166
- What?
- We're partners. aren't we?

242
00:24:15.250 --> 00:24:16.583
50/50.

243
00:24:16.666 --> 00:24:17.833
Yo. Lafleur!

244
00:24:24.875 --> 00:24:29.833
So. what. not fleeing for the hills?
You lose that lame little scooter?

245
00:24:29.916 --> 00:24:32.625
I like men who clean up nice.
but not little bitches.

246
00:24:34.375 --> 00:24:35.541
Your guy works for free.

247
00:24:35.625 --> 00:24:38.500
He sold my shit in France
without taking commission.

248
00:24:38.583 --> 00:24:39.583
Let's do it again.

249
00:24:39.666 --> 00:24:40.791
Jérôme!

250
00:24:42.250 --> 00:24:43.625
You gonna be a King?

251
00:24:45.125 --> 00:24:47.666
Yo. if you're looking for a real G.
call up your boy. SherKhan.

252
00:24:53.458 --> 00:24:54.750
Jérôme!

253
00:24:55.666 --> 00:24:56.750
Come on.

254
00:25:00.583 --> 00:25:01.583
Your mom is calling.

255
00:25:02.375 --> 00:25:03.916
Let's go. Jérôme!

256
00:25:09.000 --> 00:25:10.416
You want to know me?

257
00:25:56.416 --> 00:25:58.791
I like your guys. Punctual.

258
00:26:02.625 --> 00:26:03.625
Where are you hiding it?

259
00:26:04.541 --> 00:26:05.541
In your ass.

260
00:26:07.125 --> 00:26:08.458
Original.

261
00:26:10.708 --> 00:26:13.458
The point of using groceries
is not to hide them.

262
00:26:15.416 --> 00:26:17.916
Keeping up appearances. that's all.

263
00:26:20.791 --> 00:26:24.416
When the tide is low.
you'll all see little crabs and shrimps

264
00:26:24.500 --> 00:26:25.625
hide under the sand.

265
00:26:26.416 --> 00:26:29.583
They typically come out at night to eat.
Almost always at night.

266
00:26:30.625 --> 00:26:33.625
Okay. does anyone
have any questions about this?

267
00:26:33.708 --> 00:26:35.791
- No!
- Hmm.

268
00:26:35.875 --> 00:26:37.833
- Are you hungry?
- Yes!

269
00:26:37.916 --> 00:26:39.125
All right. let's go.

270
00:26:47.083 --> 00:26:49.416
Excuse me? So sorry.
but I can't stay any longer.

271
00:26:49.500 --> 00:26:51.833
- I was only free until noon.
- Oh. yes. yes. no problem.

272
00:26:51.916 --> 00:26:53.291
I appreciate you helping us out.

273
00:26:53.375 --> 00:26:54.791
Thanks.

274
00:26:59.750 --> 00:27:00.583
Thaïs!

275
00:27:01.750 --> 00:27:03.333
- I'm going.
- See ya!

276
00:27:13.666 --> 00:27:14.666
Nolan?

277
00:27:21.666 --> 00:27:23.625
- Who's that man?
- Uncle Jocelyn.

278
00:27:23.708 --> 00:27:25.083
Uncle Jocelyn?

279
00:27:26.125 --> 00:27:27.125
Hey. Jocelyn!

280
00:27:28.375 --> 00:27:30.250
Jocelyn! Yo!

281
00:27:33.583 --> 00:27:35.625
What the hell is he doing here?

282
00:28:04.000 --> 00:28:06.166
- What you doin' here?
- Mind your own shit. Milord!

283
00:28:12.791 --> 00:28:13.625
Get out!

284
00:28:25.500 --> 00:28:26.875
You're fucking me over.

285
00:28:26.958 --> 00:28:30.625
You're out here rambling
about how the streets will save us.

286
00:28:30.708 --> 00:28:31.875
All your bullshit.

287
00:28:31.958 --> 00:28:33.916
And you blow it all up. man.

288
00:28:34.791 --> 00:28:35.791
What for?

289
00:28:36.291 --> 00:28:38.375
Mad you're not the man of the house?

290
00:28:38.458 --> 00:28:41.125
While you're making ten kilos.
I'm making over 80.

291
00:28:42.083 --> 00:28:43.666
I buy all my shit.

292
00:28:43.750 --> 00:28:44.750
I don't steal it.

293
00:28:45.333 --> 00:28:47.291
Put it on your CV. if you want a job.

294
00:28:48.250 --> 00:28:50.666
My team dropped me 'cause of you.

295
00:28:50.750 --> 00:28:53.916
I'm in real fucking deep shit now
thanks to you.

296
00:28:54.875 --> 00:28:56.333
I want you to talk to them with me.

297
00:28:56.416 --> 00:28:58.916
- Yeah? For what?
- Tell them that you're an idiot.

298
00:28:59.000 --> 00:29:01.000
And that you're never
gonna cause problems again.

299
00:29:03.166 --> 00:29:06.458
Man. I gotta hand it to you.
You got real nerve. man.

300
00:29:07.583 --> 00:29:10.083
No one can hold a candle to you.
Respect. man.

301
00:29:10.166 --> 00:29:11.666
That's a fact.

302
00:29:12.458 --> 00:29:13.458
Ah…

303
00:29:14.041 --> 00:29:17.125
So why haven't I busted your teeth? Hmm?

304
00:29:17.208 --> 00:29:19.625
I guess I'm too kind.
Should've done it a long time ago.

305
00:29:19.708 --> 00:29:23.166
Should've yanked one out every time
you said something I didn't like.

306
00:29:23.250 --> 00:29:25.000
You'd be eating mashed potatoes.

307
00:29:25.750 --> 00:29:26.833
So get out of here.

308
00:29:28.583 --> 00:29:29.583
Yo!

309
00:29:35.875 --> 00:29:38.000
You son of a bitch piece of shit!

310
00:29:38.083 --> 00:29:39.875
What did you do with Dad?

311
00:29:39.958 --> 00:29:41.750
He's sending Jocelyn to monitor the kids?

312
00:29:41.833 --> 00:29:43.958
- Stop!
- What the fuck did you do?

313
00:29:44.041 --> 00:29:46.375
You dealing with Dad? Goddamn bastard!

314
00:29:46.958 --> 00:29:49.416
- Stop it!
- We agreed to not get them involved. yeah?

315
00:29:49.500 --> 00:29:52.708
That'd we'd keep them out!
You really are a bunch of assholes.

316
00:29:52.791 --> 00:29:54.750
You. Dad. and yeah. bro. you too!

317
00:29:55.333 --> 00:29:57.666
I swear to you.
next time he gets anywhere close to them.

318
00:29:57.750 --> 00:29:59.541
I'll goddamn destroy you!

319
00:30:04.541 --> 00:30:07.208
You're just winning hearts left and right.

320
00:30:07.291 --> 00:30:08.833
Mmm-mmm.

321
00:30:13.458 --> 00:30:14.458
Come here.

322
00:30:15.375 --> 00:30:16.916
Did Milord tell you?

323
00:30:17.541 --> 00:30:19.583
Yeah. He wants to test you.

324
00:30:19.666 --> 00:30:20.708
That's dope!

325
00:30:20.791 --> 00:30:22.333
What are we doing here?

326
00:30:22.416 --> 00:30:23.416
Scaring someone.

327
00:30:23.916 --> 00:30:24.833
Who?

328
00:30:34.208 --> 00:30:36.375
- Oh. that's Uncle Jocelyn!
- Shh!

329
00:30:37.000 --> 00:30:38.583
Damn straight we are.

330
00:30:38.666 --> 00:30:40.375
I gotta take a piss.

331
00:30:45.083 --> 00:30:46.416
Watch out.

332
00:30:55.375 --> 00:30:57.208
Man. don't you ever come near the family.

333
00:30:57.291 --> 00:30:58.166
Got it?

334
00:30:58.250 --> 00:31:00.375
You ever get within
a single block of the kids.

335
00:31:00.458 --> 00:31:03.000
I swear no one will ever find your body.

336
00:31:03.500 --> 00:31:06.416
Understood? Don't come near the family.

337
00:31:14.416 --> 00:31:15.416
Enough.

338
00:31:20.000 --> 00:31:21.875
And tell Dad the deal's the same.

339
00:31:22.375 --> 00:31:23.666
Five percent. That's it.

340
00:31:24.583 --> 00:31:26.500
We don't give in to threats.

341
00:31:29.958 --> 00:31:31.708
Ahh!

342
00:31:31.791 --> 00:31:32.958
I said enough!

343
00:31:35.416 --> 00:31:37.583
Let's go.

344
00:31:41.125 --> 00:31:42.583
Did I do well?

345
00:31:47.333 --> 00:31:48.500
Give me the gun.

346
00:31:54.416 --> 00:31:57.041
Yes. we've made a note.

347
00:32:13.625 --> 00:32:15.375
Put this on twice a day.

348
00:32:15.458 --> 00:32:19.333
After. use it as a mask on your face
and keep it damp.

349
00:32:21.416 --> 00:32:24.291
Then you rinse it off and apply ointment.

350
00:32:28.458 --> 00:32:30.291
You got a real good heart.

351
00:32:30.375 --> 00:32:33.083
Hope they pay you well at this hospital.

352
00:32:33.750 --> 00:32:34.875
It's fine.

353
00:32:36.958 --> 00:32:38.875
Not afraid they'll return?

354
00:32:39.625 --> 00:32:40.625
Who?

355
00:32:41.333 --> 00:32:42.458
The guys who did this.

356
00:32:44.208 --> 00:32:47.875
Bunch of losers. They can't scare me.

357
00:32:50.291 --> 00:32:51.500
Then who?

358
00:32:53.833 --> 00:32:54.916
Just drop it.

359
00:33:00.291 --> 00:33:01.625
You know who my cousin is?

360
00:33:04.333 --> 00:33:05.916
You know SherKhan?

361
00:33:08.166 --> 00:33:09.500
When I'm out of here…

362
00:33:10.875 --> 00:33:11.875
What?

363
00:33:12.875 --> 00:33:15.708
It won't be a "welcome home" party.
that's for damn sure.

364
00:33:16.458 --> 00:33:18.958
So don't make me better too fast.

365
00:33:21.250 --> 00:33:24.208
You know. I do spells too. if you like.

366
00:33:25.166 --> 00:33:28.458
Yeah? You can for real?

367
00:33:30.250 --> 00:33:33.333
Like… would he know it's from me?

368
00:33:35.375 --> 00:33:37.583
But it won't be anything too extreme?

369
00:33:37.666 --> 00:33:39.208
Doesn't have to be.

370
00:33:39.291 --> 00:33:40.500
Okay.

371
00:33:41.041 --> 00:33:45.375
- Don't spells need hair and shit?
- I just need a sense of his habits.

372
00:33:45.458 --> 00:33:47.000
Learn about him more.

373
00:33:47.666 --> 00:33:50.375
I need to get a visual idea
of where he goes.

374
00:33:52.750 --> 00:33:55.208
Well. he's got his bar in Trénelle.

375
00:33:55.791 --> 00:33:57.500
And he visits his mother.

376
00:33:58.000 --> 00:34:01.708
He often hangs out at the Marina du Marin.
that asshole.

377
00:34:01.791 --> 00:34:04.000
That's where his dope is shipped from.

378
00:34:05.708 --> 00:34:08.083
Hold up. SherKhan is using Croquet's boat?

379
00:34:08.166 --> 00:34:09.333
No.

380
00:34:09.416 --> 00:34:10.458
Yep.

381
00:34:12.125 --> 00:34:13.833
Man. amazing.

382
00:34:13.916 --> 00:34:15.708
You made him talk! How'd you do it?

383
00:34:15.791 --> 00:34:17.000
I'm a professional.

384
00:34:17.083 --> 00:34:18.208
One euro each.

385
00:34:18.291 --> 00:34:19.541
All right.

386
00:34:22.333 --> 00:34:25.375
Thaïs. Mathis. Nolan! Let's go home.

387
00:34:25.458 --> 00:34:27.291
We haven't finished!

388
00:34:27.958 --> 00:34:32.208
Seems to me that pretty soon
they won't have to work the stand.

389
00:34:32.791 --> 00:34:36.250
Damn straight. darling!
Our life is about to change!

390
00:36:24.333 --> 00:36:25.791
Eighty kilos on the way.

391
00:36:26.375 --> 00:36:27.375
One million euros.

392
00:36:29.041 --> 00:36:31.291
- I know.
- So what are you doing. then?

393
00:36:32.416 --> 00:36:34.250
Couldn't be sure
your other phones were safe.

394
00:36:35.083 --> 00:36:36.083
King took them.

395
00:36:36.166 --> 00:36:38.166
Don't feed me bullshit. Not one message.

396
00:36:38.250 --> 00:36:40.041
You cut me out completely.
What's happening?

397
00:36:40.958 --> 00:36:42.375
Your brother came to see us.

398
00:36:44.166 --> 00:36:45.083
Marvin.

399
00:36:46.958 --> 00:36:48.958
We can't deal with this bullshit.

400
00:36:49.041 --> 00:36:52.166
Your brother turns up. stirring up shit.
The other making trouble? Not cool.

401
00:36:53.166 --> 00:36:54.958
You gotta rein them in.

402
00:36:55.041 --> 00:36:58.125
They don't respect you.
so they don't respect any of us.

403
00:37:00.250 --> 00:37:01.583
This shit's fucked.

404
00:37:01.666 --> 00:37:02.708
I won't lie to you.

405
00:37:02.791 --> 00:37:04.791
I don't know what to tell my new buyers.

406
00:37:04.875 --> 00:37:07.000
- Meaning?
- Guys from Grenoble.

407
00:37:07.083 --> 00:37:09.875
They're solid.
They pick their coworkers carefully.

408
00:37:09.958 --> 00:37:12.791
We don't know if you're with us or not.
That'll piss them off.

409
00:37:14.416 --> 00:37:15.958
What are you planning on telling 'em?

410
00:37:17.958 --> 00:37:19.875
If they ask me. I don't know. man.

411
00:37:23.916 --> 00:37:25.333
Marvin. what'd he tell you?

412
00:37:26.250 --> 00:37:27.791
To do it without you.

413
00:37:35.458 --> 00:37:36.875
You're gonna go ahead without me?

414
00:37:37.833 --> 00:37:40.541
With everything going on.
not sure if we're gonna do any of it.

415
00:37:41.250 --> 00:37:43.458
- This shit is messy.
- I got it.

416
00:37:44.041 --> 00:37:44.958
No. you don't.

417
00:37:45.750 --> 00:37:47.666
What's that? Must've misheard you.

418
00:37:48.708 --> 00:37:51.416
You don't got shit.

419
00:38:06.541 --> 00:38:08.208
We got two choices.

420
00:38:09.041 --> 00:38:10.375
Either we go to war…

421
00:38:13.208 --> 00:38:14.708
or we get fuckin' rich.

422
00:38:22.125 --> 00:38:24.291
And how are you gonna deal with him?

423
00:38:29.916 --> 00:38:31.791
Can you send me a recent resume?

424
00:38:31.875 --> 00:38:32.916
Mmm-hmm.

425
00:38:33.833 --> 00:38:36.166
What about your time gardening
at the Balata?

426
00:38:36.250 --> 00:38:38.000
I was only there two months.

427
00:38:38.083 --> 00:38:39.875
So what? Put it.

428
00:38:41.833 --> 00:38:44.083
You gotta work on your cover letter. too.

429
00:38:47.500 --> 00:38:48.500
I'm tired.

430
00:38:49.000 --> 00:38:50.041
I know.

431
00:38:51.625 --> 00:38:55.875
SOS GARDENING
THE FIRST UBER FOR GARDENING

432
00:39:06.208 --> 00:39:08.375
It's been a shitstorm ever since Mama.

433
00:39:08.875 --> 00:39:12.458
We've got nothing to bind us.
She held us together.

434
00:39:13.916 --> 00:39:15.541
No way we're gonna make it.

435
00:39:16.125 --> 00:39:17.791
No. none of that's true.

436
00:39:18.375 --> 00:39:20.875
We're gonna grow distant
or kill each other.

437
00:39:22.541 --> 00:39:25.625
This. it's all just a rough patch.

438
00:39:25.708 --> 00:39:27.250
I know you guys.

439
00:39:27.333 --> 00:39:28.583
You're strong.

440
00:39:28.666 --> 00:39:30.375
You'll all be okay.

441
00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:33.708
You handled Kylian just as you should.

442
00:39:33.791 --> 00:39:35.416
Did what you had to do.

443
00:39:35.500 --> 00:39:37.583
That took some big balls.

444
00:39:38.333 --> 00:39:41.000
Like… a lot?

445
00:39:41.083 --> 00:39:42.291
More than two?

446
00:39:50.791 --> 00:39:52.625
- Expecting someone?
- Mmm-mmm.

447
00:40:00.208 --> 00:40:01.500
Let us in.

448
00:40:29.208 --> 00:40:30.833
What are you doing with Kylian?

449
00:40:30.916 --> 00:40:33.208
Why the fuck you here?
Why the fuck are any of you here?

450
00:40:33.291 --> 00:40:36.000
Seems we got an issue with you.

451
00:40:36.583 --> 00:40:38.750
I've been told
you were stirring up some shit.

452
00:40:38.833 --> 00:40:40.083
Came to see for myself.

453
00:40:40.958 --> 00:40:42.166
You're talking to me?

454
00:40:56.958 --> 00:40:58.000
Get the fuck out.

455
00:40:59.125 --> 00:41:00.625
Had no business talkin' to Fatso.

456
00:41:01.333 --> 00:41:03.416
It's fine. We're moving. anyway.

457
00:41:04.375 --> 00:41:07.458
But let's make a few things clear.
Don't ever come back.

458
00:41:07.541 --> 00:41:10.375
Forget about them.
Keep out of my shit. Shut your mouth.

459
00:41:11.083 --> 00:41:12.125
You got it?

460
00:41:13.166 --> 00:41:16.250
Get the fuck out my home!

461
00:41:19.416 --> 00:41:20.583
Hmm.

462
00:41:25.166 --> 00:41:26.000
Uh-uh.

463
00:41:26.500 --> 00:41:28.375
Have a bite. man. Sit down.

464
00:41:40.458 --> 00:41:42.041
You're gonna piss them off. you know.

465
00:42:00.166 --> 00:42:01.250
You're out of your minds.

466
00:42:02.791 --> 00:42:03.708
Yup.

467
00:42:04.208 --> 00:42:05.833
That's why we need a guarantee.

468
00:42:13.833 --> 00:42:15.458
- Marvin.
- Hang on.

469
00:42:15.541 --> 00:42:17.916
"Hang on"? What are you doing. Kylian?

470
00:42:18.000 --> 00:42:19.125
What's happening?

471
00:42:19.208 --> 00:42:21.125
This is just family business.

472
00:42:21.208 --> 00:42:23.541
- Let us deal with it. yeah?
- What? You're in my house!

473
00:42:23.625 --> 00:42:26.291
- Chloé. please stop. Enough.
- Hell no. I won't stop.

474
00:42:28.875 --> 00:42:32.625
Stuffing your face with my food?
I don't give a fuck.

475
00:42:34.125 --> 00:42:35.125
Kylian…

476
00:42:35.833 --> 00:42:39.916
keep up this act all you want.
but not with me.

477
00:42:40.000 --> 00:42:42.458
Could have a sleepover here too.

478
00:42:44.041 --> 00:42:46.708
Want to piss me off that badly?
In my house?

479
00:42:47.750 --> 00:42:50.500
Do you know what it means
to show up at a safehouse?

480
00:42:50.583 --> 00:42:52.958
Means you're a dead man walking.

481
00:42:53.500 --> 00:42:55.125
Means we'll rearrange your face

482
00:42:55.208 --> 00:42:58.041
till your little girlfriend
can't recognize you anymore.

483
00:42:58.916 --> 00:43:00.541
Brother or not. changes nothing.

484
00:43:00.625 --> 00:43:02.708
Don't pull that shit ever again. Marvin.

485
00:43:02.791 --> 00:43:06.166
Understand me? There are rules
and they go beyond you and I.

486
00:43:06.250 --> 00:43:09.375
So you better swear to me
that you won't be a problem.

487
00:43:11.916 --> 00:43:13.041
Swear.

488
00:43:14.375 --> 00:43:16.125
Say it. Marvin. Who cares?

489
00:43:17.875 --> 00:43:19.458
Okay.

490
00:43:21.125 --> 00:43:24.541
Do you swear that there'll
never be any more problems?

491
00:43:27.666 --> 00:43:29.166
I swear. Now beat it.

492
00:43:32.416 --> 00:43:33.833
Thank you.

493
00:44:13.083 --> 00:44:15.291
Ambre? Ambre!

494
00:44:15.375 --> 00:44:17.666
Ambre! Clean this now.

495
00:44:21.125 --> 00:44:23.916
<i>Workin' hard. money's tight</i>
<i>No matter how hard we try</i>

496
00:44:24.000 --> 00:44:27.083
<i>They're waiting for your decline</i>
<i>Show's over 'cause we ain't got a dime </i>

497
00:44:27.166 --> 00:44:30.208
<i>Don't give a fuck what you think</i>
<i>I won't waste my time </i>

498
00:44:30.291 --> 00:44:32.291
<i>Been feelin' dead inside</i>
<i>Since she passed</i>

499
00:44:32.375 --> 00:44:33.708
<i>Got my heart feeling tight</i>

500
00:44:33.791 --> 00:44:36.541
<i>Sandmen. slumlords</i>
<i>I'm wipin' them out just the same</i>

501
00:44:36.625 --> 00:44:39.500
<i>Fuck this shitty life</i>
<i>These rhymes are my escape</i>

502
00:44:39.583 --> 00:44:42.958
<i>I want to succeed</i>
<i>I want to work hard and touch the sky</i>

503
00:44:43.041 --> 00:44:46.250
<i>Sandmen. slumlords</i>
<i>I'm wipin' them out just the same…</i>

504
00:44:46.333 --> 00:44:49.000
Hey!

505
00:44:49.625 --> 00:44:51.833
Hey! Whoo!

506
00:45:22.041 --> 00:45:23.625
Why'd you bring me here?

507
00:45:24.833 --> 00:45:28.291
Got no place to go.
Not welcome at the house anymore.

508
00:45:30.541 --> 00:45:32.166
Wasn't my decision.

509
00:45:33.791 --> 00:45:34.791
Sure.

510
00:45:35.625 --> 00:45:36.791
Never mind.

511
00:45:39.583 --> 00:45:42.416
I'm better off among the dead
than among the living.

512
00:45:59.291 --> 00:46:00.500
What's that?

513
00:46:01.500 --> 00:46:02.916
It's my shipment.

514
00:46:05.375 --> 00:46:07.291
- How much?
- Taping me?

515
00:46:07.375 --> 00:46:09.750
Are you serious? Come on!

516
00:46:09.833 --> 00:46:11.000
I'm kidding.

517
00:46:13.958 --> 00:46:15.375
Why did you ask me here?

518
00:46:15.875 --> 00:46:19.125
I'll tell you.
But first. I gotta ask you something.

519
00:46:20.625 --> 00:46:23.541
If Marvin and King find out I'm with you.
I'm a dead woman.

520
00:46:24.541 --> 00:46:26.000
Last time. how much did you make?

521
00:46:27.625 --> 00:46:28.750
Four hundred.

522
00:46:29.250 --> 00:46:30.625
How many kilos?

523
00:46:30.708 --> 00:46:31.750
Twenty.

524
00:46:33.416 --> 00:46:34.625
We got eighty.

525
00:46:36.708 --> 00:46:40.416
I got guys in Grenoble who are buying.
but I might have an issue with them.

526
00:46:40.916 --> 00:46:41.833
Why's that?

527
00:46:42.333 --> 00:46:45.625
One of my guys set it all up.
but now I got some problems.

528
00:46:45.708 --> 00:46:47.333
He's not trustworthy.

529
00:46:52.083 --> 00:46:54.000
- The guy you worked with--
- Xhésus.

530
00:46:54.083 --> 00:46:55.166
Xhésus.

531
00:46:55.958 --> 00:46:57.500
You want his digits.

532
00:46:57.583 --> 00:46:58.500
Yeah.

533
00:47:00.833 --> 00:47:03.166
You're still gonna
need someone over there to receive it.

534
00:47:03.250 --> 00:47:04.958
Fatso will be there.

535
00:47:05.041 --> 00:47:06.166
Let me do it.

536
00:47:06.250 --> 00:47:07.500
What? No.

537
00:47:09.458 --> 00:47:10.750
No Xhésus. then.

538
00:47:17.041 --> 00:47:19.125
- All right. I'm off.
- Hang on.

539
00:47:19.625 --> 00:47:20.750
What?

540
00:47:26.041 --> 00:47:27.291
Belle?

541
00:47:28.625 --> 00:47:30.666
- Why is she here?
- Xhésus is her contact.

542
00:47:30.750 --> 00:47:32.541
- What?
- So she's going with you.

543
00:47:33.625 --> 00:47:35.583
Hell no. You better be joking.

544
00:47:36.375 --> 00:47:38.333
You brought this on yourself. man.

545
00:47:38.833 --> 00:47:41.916
You. Peace. K2R.
you forced me to go after my brother.

546
00:47:42.541 --> 00:47:43.750
So this is revenge?

547
00:47:43.833 --> 00:47:45.208
I make changes accordingly.

548
00:47:47.541 --> 00:47:50.666
So we were wrong about your brother?
Should've ignored him?

549
00:47:50.750 --> 00:47:54.458
No. of course not. but all you had to do
was tell me that my brother talked to you.

550
00:47:54.541 --> 00:47:56.083
I would've dealt with him on my own.

551
00:47:56.916 --> 00:47:58.333
You were testing me. Okay.

552
00:47:58.416 --> 00:48:01.000
Let's put everyone to the test.
back to square one.

553
00:48:01.083 --> 00:48:05.541
Everybody's a blank slate.
and right now. Annabelle is going. period.

554
00:48:09.666 --> 00:48:12.250
Do what needs to be done. Don't fuck up.

555
00:49:30.291 --> 00:49:31.375
Everyone out!

556
00:49:31.458 --> 00:49:32.625
There's smoke. let's go!

557
00:49:32.708 --> 00:49:33.833
Move. go. go!

558
00:49:34.333 --> 00:49:35.916
Let's go. hurry up.

559
00:49:37.375 --> 00:49:40.416
Léo! Where's Léo? Where is he?

560
00:49:40.500 --> 00:49:42.541
It's okay. he's at soccer. Let's go.

561
00:49:43.041 --> 00:49:45.375
Go. run. run! You sure?

562
00:49:45.458 --> 00:49:46.583
Yes.

563
00:49:52.666 --> 00:49:55.666
Léo! Léo. are you there?

564
00:49:56.166 --> 00:49:58.083
God damn it!
